text.section:
The transferor may:
As declarant serve as trustee;
Designate a trustee;
Designate how the trustee will be chosen;
Designate successor trustees in the order in which they will serve; and
Designate how successor trustees will be chosen.

The next willing successor trustee in line shall accept the records and trust property and become trustee as soon as practicable after:
The resignation of the trustee;
The declination of the trustee;
The death of the trustee; or
The removal of the trustee.

If the trustee is unable or unwilling to serve and no successor trustee will serve, the following persons in the order listed may petition the court to designate a successor trustee:
The transferor or the legal representative of the transferor;
The trustee;
The beneficiary or the beneficiary's legal representative;
The guardian of the person of the beneficiary;
An adult member of the beneficiary's family or that family member's legal representative; or
A person interested in the trust property or a person interested in the welfare of the beneficiary, either of whom the court determines to have a legitimate interest.
